main event: A witness observed a white, dome-shaped object moving from north to south over Omaha, Nebraska, for approximately 3-4 minutes on October 7, 1967.
interesting points: The object appeared bright and made no noise while moving at a constant speed., Witnesses noted the object passed behind clouds and had no visible means of propulsion., Local investigations questioned the reliability of the witness., The object was seen at the altitude of approximately 2000 to 2100 ft., The report suggested a conclusion of probable aircraft but marked it as insufficient clarity.
witness description: The primary witness reported observing the object for about 3-4 minutes.
